<p><strong>Unveiling the Secrets of the Snowden Files</strong></p>
<p><strong>Q: Who is Luke Harding and what is his connection to the Snowden Files?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Luke Harding is an award-winning British journalist and foreign correspondent for The Guardian. He played a pivotal role in breaking the story of the Snowden Files, a massive leak of classified US government documents by former CIA contractor Edward Snowden.</p>
<p><strong>Q: What do the Snowden Files contain and why are they significant?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> The Snowden Files consist of over 1.7 million documents that expose the extensive surveillance programs conducted by the US government and its allies. They reveal the existence of secret spy programs, data collection on millions of people, and the targeting of foreign leaders. The files have sparked global outrage and raised serious concerns about government overreach.</p>
<p><strong>Q: How did Luke Harding obtain the Snowden Files?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Harding was one of the first journalists to meet with Snowden in Hong Kong in 2013. Snowden trusted Harding with access to the files, believing that The Guardian would handle them responsibly and bring them to the public's attention.</p>
<p><strong>Q: What is the significance of Harding's book, "The Snowden Files"?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> Harding's book, "The Snowden Files: The Inside Story of the World's Most Wanted Man," provides an in-depth account of the Snowden affair. It explores the events leading up to the leak, the aftermath, and the global impact of the revelations. The book has been praised for its detailed reporting and insights into the motivations of Snowden.</p>
<p><strong>Q: Can I access the Snowden Files?</strong></p>
<p><strong>A:</strong> The full Snowden Files are available online at The Guardian's website. However, you can also download a PDF version of Luke Harding's book, "The Snowden Files," to get a comprehensive understanding of the leak and its implications. The PDF version of the book is available for purchase on Amazon and other online retailers.</p>